list.abstract: launch（英 [lɔːntʃ]，美 [lɔːntʃ]），英语单词，作动词为使（船）下水；开始；创办。作名词为发射；发起；大汽艇。短语搭配有launch a business venture（创办企业）、launch a campaign（发起运动）。例句为“Launch a manned spacecraft to Mars（向火星发射一艘载人飞船）”。 launch相关近义词有release、send等，相关反义词有abolish。

yingyinNormal.en: We're going to have to launch as soon as possible, which changes our travel time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们只能尽快发射来改变航程时间。

yingyinNormal.en: Still going after launch codes? Yes he is, but he's not making any head way.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还在查发射密码？没错，但他并没什么进展。

yingyinNormal.en: So those are the launch tubes. So the actual explosive, the fireworks are stuffed in those. Yes. Right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些是发射管，炸药、烟花被塞进里面。是的。对。

yingyinNormal.en: You run a whorehouse, not an orbital launch facility. Fine. I'd like to make some changes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你经营的是妓院，不是轨道发射设施。好吧，我想要做一些更改。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, Professor Proton. Hey, thanks for being here. No problem. I'm on my "Launch" break.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好啊，质子教授。谢谢你的大驾光临。小事啦。我发射[午饭]休息时间刚好有空。

yingyinNormal.en: Block all exits, cut off their supplies. You make it impossible for them to launch their hovercrafts. Bury them alive.
yingyinNormal.zh: 封堵所有出口，切断一切供给，使他们无法发射自己的飞行器。活埋他们。

yingyinNormal.en: There is an electric match, together with the shell. When the electric match ignites, the shell is going to propel from the launch tube.
yingyinNormal.zh: 烟花弹配有电子火柴。一旦电子火柴打火，烟花弹就从发射管升空。

yingyinNormal.en: Nice story. Anyway, the reason I wanted to talk to you is NASA has moved up my launch to the International Space Station.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真是好故事，总之，我想跟你谈谈的原因是宇航局把我上太空站的发射提前了。

yingyinNormal.en: That's the long shot. There's a Plan A and a Plan B. Did you notice anything strange about the launch chamber?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那才是真正的赌注，有个A计划 ，还有个B计划，你发现发射室有什么奇怪的地方吗？

yingyinNormal.en: If you launch those helicarriers today, Hydra will be able to kill anyone that stands in their way, unless we stop them.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你们今天发射了那些天空母舰，九头蛇就能杀掉任何阻碍他们的人，除非我们阻止他们。

yingyinNormal.en: This made possible by IMF agents who did willing provide the launch codes to a known terrorist. Do I have that right, agent Brandt?
yingyinNormal.zh: 而这一切的起因，都是因为碟中谍小组的特工故意将导弹发射密码透漏给一个恐怖分子，我说对了吗，勃兰特特工？

yingyinNormal.en: But you know what wasn't a party? That hotel in Kazakhstan they put you up in before the launch. I mean, it's your last night on Earth. You'd think you'd get one porn channel.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们知道什么绝不算派对吗？火箭发射前的一晚我被安排入住哈萨克斯坦的酒店，那可是我待在地球的最后一晚，还以为会送个黄片频道看看呢。

yingyinNormal.en: He worked on the Mars rover. He helped launch the New Horizons space probe. He went to space on a Russian rocket. And I was scared the whole time. And I was scared for you, but also proud.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他操作过火星漫游者。他帮助发射了新地平线航天探测器。他乘坐俄国的火箭上过太空。当时我一直很害怕。我也为你害怕，但同时也为你骄傲。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, well, it's really cool. You fly to Moscow, they take you out to Kazakhstan, and then you get into a Russian Soyuz rocket which shoots you into a low earth orbit. Or just sits there on the launch pad because the Kazakhi mafia sold the rocket fuel on the black market.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个过程就酷了，你先飞到莫斯科 然后他们带你去哈萨克斯坦，然后你再登上一个俄罗斯联盟号火箭，直接冲上低空地球轨道，又或是你只能呆坐在火箭发射台上，因为哈萨克黑手党把火箭燃料都拿到黑市上去卖了。

yingyinNormal.en: Computer, launch TOR. Go to Cloak and Veil.
yingyinNormal.zh: 电脑，打开洋葱代理，搜索「披风和面纱」。

yingyinNormal.en: SpaceX is currently developing a fully and rapidly reusable launch system.
yingyinNormal.zh: SpaceX公司目前正在研发一种充分快速的可重复使用的运载系统。

yingyinNormal.en: That's as good as new. Hooray. Now we test it. Prepare for launch. Aye, aye.
yingyinNormal.zh: 瞧啊，像新的一样太棒了。现在我们要出海了。遵命。

yingyinNormal.en: See, it's stuff like this that gives me trust issues. We have to stop the launch.
yingyinNormal.zh: 瞧，就是因为这种人，害得我不敢相信别人。我们得阻止它起飞。

yingyinNormal.en: So, the question is: who in S.H.I.E.L.D could launch a domestic missile strike? Pierce.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在的问题是局里谁有权发动国内导弹袭击。皮尔斯。

yingyinNormal.en: It's our job to make them money, but once we launch this little baby, they're gonna flip.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们是来帮他们赚钱的，我们推出这个宝贝时，他们可要乐坏了。

exam_freq_info.chinese: 发起; 推出; 创立

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: start or set in motion an activity or enterprise
sense_info_list.zh: 发起; 推出; 创立

examination_example.sentence: Michelle Obama has <highlight>launched</highlight> a high-visibility campaign against childhood obesity, even claiming that it represents our greatest national security threat.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 米歇尔·奥巴马发起了一场针对儿童肥胖的高调运动，甚至声称这是我们国家安全的最大威胁。

examination_example.sentence: The Breakthrough Prize in Life Sciences, <highlight>launched</highlight> this year, takes an unrepresentative view of what the life sciences include.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 今年推出的生命科学突破奖对生命科学的内容采取了一种不具代表性的观点。

examination_example.sentence: That's one reason why we have <highlight>launched</highlight> Arc, a new publication dedicated to the near future.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这也是我们推出Arc的原因之一，这是一本致力于近期发展的新刊物。

sense_info_list.en: to send something out, such as a new ship into the water or a spacecraft into space

direction_info.description:

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: A new space policy is focused on managing the increasing number of satellites that companies and governments are <highlight>launching</highlight> into space.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一项新的太空政策着重于管理由公司和政府向太空发射的越来越多的卫星。

examination_example.sentence: Newly <highlight>launched</highlight> satellites don't use radio frequencies that would interfere with existing satellites, and schedule when such new satellites can be <highlight>launched</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 新发射的卫星不会使用干扰现有卫星的无线电频率，并会计划何时发射此类新卫星。

examination_example.sentence: Space, especially the space directly around our planet, is getting more crowded as more governments and companies <highlight>launch</highlight> satellites.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着越来越多的政府和公司发射卫星，空间，尤其是我们星球周围的空间变得越来越拥挤。

sense_info_list.en: start an activity, especially an organized one

examination_example.sentence: A global campaign has been <highlight>launched</highlight> to create a network of ocean sanctuaries to protect the seas in the region.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一项旨在建立海洋保护区网络以保护该地区海洋的全球运动已经启动。

examination_example.sentence: By offering instant discounts worth as much as $100, DeWalt <highlight>launched</highlight> a trade-in program to encourage people to bring back tools.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 得伟公司推出了折价换新计划，为参与者提供高达100美元的即时折扣，鼓励更多人把旧工具送去回收。

examination_example.sentence: Since the <highlight>launch</highlight> of its program, Best Buy changed its policy to add a $25 fee for recycling old televisions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 项目推出后，百思买对政策进行调整，增加了25美元的旧电视回收费。

examination_example.sentence: When companies <highlight>launch</highlight> environmental programs, they will have their brand reputation enhanced.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 企业发起环保项目将有助于提升品牌声誉。

examination_example.sentence: The Nature Conservancy <highlight>launched</highlight> a fierce war against the pigs, complete with helicopters and sharp shooters. And it worked.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大自然保护协会(Nature Conservancy)用直升机和狙击手与野猪之间展开了一场激烈的战争，而且该行为很有效。

sense_info_list.en: start or set in motion an activity or enterprise

examination_example.sentence: In 2009, he and his wife Laura <highlight>launched</highlight> Maple Hill Creamery, an organic, all grass-fed yogurt company in Northern New York.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 2009年，他和他的妻子创立了 Maple Hill Creamery(枫叶山乳脂制造产厂)，一家位于纽约北部的全草饲有机酸奶公司。

sense_info_list.en: introduce a new product or publication to the public for the first time

examination_example.sentence: In February they made adjustments to the format, dropping some catwalk items immediately and promising that others would <highlight>launch</highlight> in the coming months.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 今年2月，他们对款式进行了调整，立即放弃了一些t台服装，并承诺其他服装将在未来几个月推出。

examination_example.sentence: Soon after <highlight>launching</highlight> E Pic's most successful product-the Bison Bacon Cranberry Bar-Collinsand Forrest found they'd exhausted their sources for bison (北美野牛) raised exclusively on pasture.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在推出EPIC最成功的产品 Bison Bacon Cranberry Bar(北美野牛培根蔓越莓棒)之后不久，Collins 和 Forrest 发现他们已经用尽了仅在牧场上饲养的北美野牛资源。

sense_info_list.en: start an activity; especially an organized one

examination_example.sentence: The family is offering a reward for the safe return of the dog after <highlight>launching</highlight> a social media campaign to find the thief.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这家人在社交媒体上发起了寻找窃贼的活动，并给予悬赏，希望能让狗狗安全回家。

examination_example.sentence: In fall 2010, she helped <highlight>launch</highlight> a pilot project in Chicago to see if the iPad could improve working conditions and patient care.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 2010年秋天，她帮助在芝加哥启动了一个试点项目，确认iPad能否改善工作条件和病人护理。

examination_example.sentence: The federal Head Start program, <highlight>launched</highlight> 50 years ago, has served more than 30 million children.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 50年前启动的联邦启智计划已经为3000多万儿童提供了服务。

examination_example.sentence: A pair of entrepreneurs are planning to build and <highlight>launch</highlight> a spacecraft that would carry and roast coffee beans in outer space.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一对企业家正计划建造和发射一个可以在外太空携带和烘焙咖啡豆的航天器。

examination_example.sentence: The Olympic <highlight>launched</highlight> first in 1910, followed by the Titanic in 1911, and lastly the Britannic in 1914.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 奥林匹克号于1910年首先下水航行，紧随其后的是1911年泰坦尼克号，最后是1914年的不列颠尼克号。

sense_info_list.en: start or set in motion an activity or enterprise

examination_example.sentence: Others in the US have found similar effects with National Institutes of Health early-career fellowships <highlight>launching</highlight> narrow winners far ahead of close losers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国的其他人也发现了类似的效应，即美国国立卫生研究院的早期职业研究项目中，小赢家远远领先于小输家。

examination_example.sentence: Starting businesses of their own, and even <highlight>launching</highlight> business ventures that eventually may fail, all indicate "initiative," "creativity," and "adaptability" .
examination_example.sentence_trans: 自己创业，甚至开始可能最终失败的商业冒险，都体现出“主动性”、“创造性”和“适应性”。

sense_info_list.en: introduce a new product or publication to the public for the first time

examination_example.sentence: New York-based Jump Bikes is already operating an electric bikeshare in Washington, D. C. , and is <highlight>launching</highlight> in San Francisco Thursday.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 总部位于纽约的Jump Bikes已经在华盛顿特区运营电动自行车共享服务，并将于周四在旧金山推出。

examination_example.sentence: With the development of China, we have already owned three other famous satellite <highlight>launch</highlight> centers — Jiuquan, Taiyuan and Wenchang.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着中国的发展，我们已经拥有另外三个著名的卫星发射中心——酒泉、太原和文昌。

examination_example.sentence: Where did China <highlight>launch</highlight> the last satellite of the third-generation network?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 中国第三代网络最后一颗卫星是在哪里发射的？

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>launch</highlight> showed our country has completed our largest space-based system.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这次发射表明我们国家已经完成了我们最大的天基系统。

sense_info_list.en: start or set in motion an activity or enterprise

examination_example.sentence: Since March last year, the governments have <highlight>launched</highlight> a lot of policies.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 自去年3月以来，各国政府推出了许多政策。

examination_example.sentence: Following these policies, the primary school <highlight>launched</highlight> an "agricultural (农业的) class base" on one of its schoolyards.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据这些政策，这所小学在它的一个校园里建立了一个“农业班级基地”。
